author: Staff Reports
title: Prep roundup, Oct. 20
text: Follow @jdnsports Posted Oct. 21, 2015 at 6:00 AM ROCKY MOUNT | Rocky Mount, undefeated and tied for No. 3 in the latest N.C. Tennis Coaches Association 3-A rankings, swept past Jacksonville 6-0 on Tuesday in the first round of the NCHSAA 3-A girls’ tennis playoffs. The Cardinals, who won the Coastal Conference for the third time in four years, finish 12-2. “Today was tough,” JHS coach David Fleischer said. “Actually, some of those matches, especially at three through six, were a little closer than the scores indicate. We only played singles and it was a solid two hours. “We couldn’t ask much more from these girls considering we lost our top two players from last year. We have five of six back and next year I expect us to win the conference and maybe with an older team be able to compete a little better in the first round of the playoffs.” SINGLES: Bryant (RM) d. Henderson 6-1, 6-0; Brice (RM) d. George 6-1, 6-0; Fike (RM) d. Long 7-6 (7-4), 6-0; Thompson (RM) d. Ingraham 6-1, 6-0; Bland (RM) d. Oswalt 6-2, 6-1; Warner (RM) d. Strout 6-2, 6-3. DOUBLES: Not played RECORDS: JHS 12-2, season complete. RM: 13-0, vs. Cornith Holders-Rockingham Co. winner Tuesday. Beddingfield 6, Croatan 2: Croatan won two singles matches and took a third to a tiebreaker but it wasn’t enough as the Cougars fell to Beddingfield in the opening round of the NCHSAA 2-A playoffs at Fike High School. Croatan finishes the season 9-7. “Two evenly matched teams,” coach Jim Sheehan said, “We were just unfortunate. They played well and won a lot of big points.” SINGLES: Beamon (B) d. LeBlanc 6-1, 6-1; Sullivan (B) d. Bass 6-4, 6-2; A. Desmone (C) d. Wasilewski 6-4, 4-6, 10-6; Hayes (B) d. Daas 6-1, 4-6, 10-5; Gear (B) d. D’Amico 6-3, 6-1; M. Desmone (C) d. Little 6-4, 6-0. DOUBLES: Beamon-Sullivan (B) d. LeBlanc-Daas 8-2; Hayes-Gear (B) d. M. Desmone-J. Lorenzo 8-0; (third doubles didn’t finish with Croatan up 4-3). RECORDS: C: 9-7, season complete. B: 15-4, vs. NCSSM-Wheatmore winner Tuesday. VOLLEYBALL Jacksonville 3, White Oak 1: Claire Kellum had 5 kills, 3 aces, 2 blocks and a dozen assists as Jacksonville beat White Oak in a Coastal 3-A Conference match that marked the end of the regular season for both teams. The Cardinals (10-7) finished tied for fourth with Swansboro at 6-6. The teams split during the regular season, but the Cardinals earned the fourth seed for playoff seedings because they beat a higher seed (West Craven) than the Pirates. WO: NA. RECORDS –JHS: 10-7 6-6, state playoffs TBA. WO: 4-16, 0-12, season complete. Page 2 of 3 - Richlands 3, Swansboro 0: Darby Baysden had 28 assists and 13 service points, including 3 aces, as Richlands swept Swansboro in a Coastal 3-A Conference match that ended the regular season for both teams. The NCHSAA is scheduled to announce the playoff pairings Thursday. Richlands (12-8, 8-4) earned the third and last guaranteed playoff spot the league receives while Swansboro (10-9, 6-6) is expected to get a postseason berth as a wild card. Swansboro tied with Jacksonville at 6-6 for fourth in the league. The teams split their matches, but JHS earned the fourth spot for playoff seedings because it beat a higher seeded team (West Craven) than Swansboro. Croatan 3, Dixon 0: Led by Polly Watts’ seven aces and 3 kills, Croatan closed out the regular season with a sweep of Dixon in an East Central 2-A Conference match in Broad Creek. As league champions, the Cougars (15-3, 9-1) earned the ECC’s No. 1 playoff seed. Dixon (8-11, 6-4) tied with North Brunswick (11-12, 6-4) for third, but the Bulldogs beat North Brunswick twice, giving the Bulldogs the last of three guaranteed playoff sports out of the ECC. The NCHSAA is scheduled to release the playoff brackets Thursday.
